<h1>Problem 438 - 2012 EGMO, P7 of 8, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute-angled triangle with circumcircle \(\Gamma\) and orthocentre \(H\). Let \(K\) be a point of \(\Gamma\) on the other side of \(BC\) from \(A\). Let \(L\) be the reflection of \(K\) in the line \(AB\), and let \(M\) be the reflection of \(K\) in the line \(BC\). Let \(E\) be the second point of intersection of \(\Gamma\) with the circumcircle of triangle \(BLM\).</p>
<p>Show that the lines \(KH\), \(EM\) and \(BC\) are concurrent. (The orthocentre of a triangle is the point on all three of its altitudes.)</p>
